name: Fish[think]TANK
description:
Fish[think]TANK
Illustration by Kelly De Meyer

A limited edition print on high quality matt satin photopaper. Edition of 30. All signed, numbered and with a stamp of authenticity. Size is 40 by 40 cm. 

A serie of 5 illustrations for an article for Litmusphere magazine (Australia) about prisoner movies. That weird sub genre of horror movies. Where people are hunted down by something or someone unindentified, even get tortured by a demon within themselfs.

name: 'Guerilla Green'
description:
'Guerilla Green' 
Illustration by Kelly De Meyer

An A3 print on high quality matt satin photopaper. Limited edition of 30. All signed, numbered and with a stamp of authenticity.

A short children's story about Pit the sunflower seed and his trip around the world. More info about the project you can read in an feature at nonewenemies.net.

Follow Pit The Seed on his journey.

name: 'Shaved Or Natural'
description:
'Shaved Or Natural' 
Illustration by Kelly De Meyer

An A3 print on high quality matt satin photopaper. 
Limited edition of 30. All signed, numbered and with a stamp of authenticity. 

This is a short story about the twin sisters Puakenikeni and their 2 kittens.  

They take you through a journey of dealing with the everyday challenges:  puberty,  sexuality, hypertrichosis, desire and longing, peer pressure, the struggle with finding the balance between conforming and self acceptance. 

This is a illustration I did for an all female group exhibition at 182a Gallery in Rotterdam last year.

The booklet with the short story about the twin sisters will be available shortly.
